President Obama and his wife Michelle extend their warmest wishes to those celebrating Hanukkah worldwide. They acknowledge the significance of the Hanukkah story, which highlights the power of faith and perseverance in overcoming adversity. They emphasize that Hanukkah is not just a celebration for the Jewish community, but an opportunity for people of all faiths to come together and celebrate common aspirations. The President encourages individuals to find inspiration in Hanukkah's lessons, to be grateful for their blessings, to find light in dark times, and to work collectively towards a brighter future.